text: Tulsa County's first positive Covid-19 case has recovered. This individual has had two negative tests, which is the indicator of recovery.
claimReview_0_textualRating: Correct, this patient has recovered according to official Tulsa County sources. Two negative tests is one of three official indicators of recovery among people with Covid-19 (who showed symptoms).

text: All seven patients who were getting treated for Covid-19 at Safdarjung hospital in New Delhi have recovered.
claimReview_0_textualRating: There is a news story reporting that seven patients in this hospital in New Delhi had recovered. However, these were not the only Covid-19 patients in the city.

text: Doctors in India have been successful in treating coronavirus with a combination of drugs (Lopinavir, Retonovir, Oseltamivir along with Chlorphenamine) and are going to suggest the same medicine globally.
claimReview_0_textualRating: India’s ministry of health has advised that the anti-HIV drugs, Lopinavir and Retonovir, are used in some groups of Covid-19 patients. But it is unclear how successful this treatment has been. The other two drugs from the claim are not mentioned in their guidance.

text: Apple has reopened all 42 China stores.
claimReview_0_textualRating: Correct. On 13 March 2020, Apple announced that it had reopened all 42 stores in mainland China after a closure of almost six weeks.

text: A network of Canadian scientists are making excellent progress in Covid-19 research.
claimReview_0_textualRating: At least one group of Canadian scientists has recently announced some progress in understanding Covid-19.

text: Three Maryland coronavirus patients fully recovered and are able to return to everyday life.
claimReview_0_textualRating: Correct. On 13 March 2020, Montgomery County, Maryland confirmed that three residents who previously had the virus no longer tested positive.

text: Plasma from newly recovered patients from Covid -19 can treat others infected by Covid-19.
claimReview_0_textualRating: This is being used as a treatment in some countries, but clinical trials have not yet proved that this is effective.

text: A San Diego biotech company is developing a Covid-19 vaccine in collaboration with Duke University and National University of Singapore.
claimReview_0_textualRating: This is correct. The company, Arcturus Therapeutics, announced on 4 March 2020 that it would be working on a vaccine with DukeNUS Medical School in Singapore.

text: Researchers at the Erasmus Medical Center claim to have found an antibody against coronavirus.
claimReview_0_textualRating: Researchers in the Netherlands have released research, which has not yet been peer-reviewed, on an antibody against the new coronavirus.

text: The number of new cases in South Korea is declining.
claimReview_0_textualRating: This was correct when the viral post began to appear. Reported new cases declined from their peak in late February, and have been roughly level since mid-March

text: Cleveland Clinic developed a Covid-19 test that gives results in hours, not days.
claimReview_0_textualRating: This is incorrect. The clinic announced that it is able to speed up Covid-19 testing after developing the ability to test on-site, but it had not developed a new test.

text: Italy is hit hard, experts say, only because they have the oldest population in Europe.
claimReview_0_textualRating: Whilst it is true that an older population has contributed to a high number of deaths in Italy, it may not be the sole reason.
